    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-04-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-04-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="569"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d569">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00118 European War 1939/1920</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 10948</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-04-22">April 22,
                            1943</date>.<lb/>[Received April 30.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to report that Aranha<note
                        n="27" xml:id="d569fn27">Oswaldo Aranha, Brazilian Minister for Foreign
                        Affairs.</note> told me today that the Brazilian Government hopes that the
                    Brazilian Military Mission now in North Africa (my telegrams Nos. 906 of
                    February 22, 5 p.m. and 1229 of March 12, 4 p.m.)<note n="28" xml:id="d569fn28"
                        >Neither printed.</note> will be allowed to remain there indefinitely. He
                    added that he hoped that a rumor that had reached him that they would be
                    permitted to stay only six weeks was untrue.</p>
                <p>Respectfully yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Jefferson Caffery</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
